    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Pratik Bhandari\"\nabout:\n  template: marquee\n  image-width: 10em\n  image-shape: round\n  image: me.png\n  links:\n    - icon: twitter\n      text: twitter\n      href: \"https://twitter.com/prbhx\"\n    - icon: person-circle\n      text: scholar\n      href: \"https://scholar.google.de/citations?user=Y0HnEQwAAAAJ&hl=en&oi=ao\"\n    - icon: book\n      text: publications\n      href: \"https://sites.google.com/view/pratik-bhandari/publications\"\n    # - icon: github\n    #   text: Github\n    #   href: https://github.com/pratik-bhandari\n---\n\nHello there! Welcome to my site.\n\nI am a doctoral researcher at the Collaborative Research Center (Sonderforschungsbereichs -- [SFB 1102](https://sfb1102.uni-saarland.de)) at Saarland University, Department of Psychology and Department of Language Science and Technology. [Prof. Jutta Kray](https://www.uni-saarland.de/lehrstuhl/kray/team/jk.html) and [Prof. Vera Demberg](https://www.uni-saarland.de/lehrstuhl/demberg/members/verademberg.html) are my advisors.\n\nMy PhD research is focused on how we make sense of spoken language under adverse listening conditions.\nI study when (and how) context helps us understand degraded speech,\nand when context is not much helpful.\n\nI expect to complete my PhD by the end of September this year. Offers for postdoc positions are welcome :)\n\n---\n\n## Education\n\n**Saarland University** **|** Germany\\\nPhD **|** Nov 2018 - Sep 2022 (*expected*)\n\n**Basque Center on Cognition, Brain and Language** **|** Spain\\\nMaster in Cognitive Neuroscience of Language **|** Sep 2017 - Sep 2018\n\n**Institute of Medicine**, Tribhuvan University **|** Nepal\\\nBachelor in Audiology & Speech-Language Pathology **|** Nov 2010 - April 2015\n\n---\n\n## Experience\n\n**Action Conrol and Cognition Lab**, U of Hyderabad, India **|** Research Intern **|** Dec 2015 - May 2017\n\n**BnC Medical College Teaching Hospital**, Nepal **|** Audiologist & Speech Pathologist **|** April 2015 - Dec 2015\n\n---\n\n## Selected publications\n\n**Bhandari, P.**, Demberg, V., & Kray, J. (2021). Semantic predictability facilitates\ncomprehension of degraded speech in a graded manner. *Frontiers in Psychology*, 3769. [[doi](10.3389/fpsyg.2021.714485)]\n\n**Bhandari, P.**, Prasad, S., & Mishra, R.K. (2020). High proficient bilinguals bring in higher executive control when encountering diverse interlocutors. *Journal of Cultural Cognitive Science. 4*(2), 201-215. [[doi](10.1007/s41809-020-00060-7)]\n\n**Bhandari, P.**, & Khanal, P. (2016). Pride in autistic diversity: Against treatment or for inclusion? *The Lancet, 388*(10059), 24477. [[doi](10.1016/S0140-6736(16)32176-6)]\n\n---\n\n<!--\n\n \n\nThis is a place of my musing.\n\n[Here](https://pratik-bhandari.github.io/), [I](https://sites.google.com/view/pratik-bhandari) jot down some semi-filtered thoughts, opinions, and experiences.\\\n\nCheck out some [poetry, stories](https://pratik-bhandari.github.io/literature.html), and other [artwork](https://pratik-bhandari.github.io/art.html).\n\nDon't forget to contact me via any of the means below!\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n|       |                  |\n|-------|------------------|\n|       |                  |\n| ![](me.png){width=95%} | ::: {.cell-output-display}\n`<svg aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\" viewBox=\"0 0 496 512\" style=\"height:1em;width:0.97em;vertical-align:-0.125em;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;font-size:inherit;fill:currentColor;overflow:visible;position:relative;\"><path d=\"M248 8C111 8 0 119 0 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S385 8 248 8zm0 96c48.6 0 88 39.4 88 88s-39.4 88-88 88-88-39.4-88-88 39.4-88 88-88zm0 344c-58.7 0-111.3-26.6-146.5-68.2 18.8-35.4 55.6-59.8 98.5-59.8 2.4 0 4.8.4 7.1 1.1 13 4.2 26.6 6.9 40.9 6.9 14.3 0 28-2.7 40.9-6.9 2.3-.7 4.7-1.1 7.1-1.1 42.9 0 79.7 24.4 98.5 59.8C359.3 421.4 306.7 448 248 448z\"/></svg>`{=html}\n:::\n\n [academic profile](https://sites.google.com/view/pratik-bhandari/publications) <br